nerateSQL\" calloutDescription=\"Generate a drop table statement\" calloutFilterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction/GenerateDropStatement/ReadDropStatementFromFile\" calloutFilterValue=\"1\" calloutLabel=\"Generate\" calloutRequiresConnection=\"true\" calloutType=\"builder\"><CalloutArgument name=\"statementType\">DropTableSQL</CalloutArgument></Callout></Callouts></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"true\" description=\"Specifies whether to generate a truncate table statement at runtime\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction\" filterValue=\"3\" label=\"Generate truncate statement at runtime\" maxOccurs=\"1\" name=\"GenerateTruncateStatement\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Abort the job if there is an error executing a command\" label=\"Fail on error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnError\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select YES to read the TRUNCATE statement from the file that is specified in the TRUNCATE statement property.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction/GenerateTruncateStatement\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Read truncate statement from file\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"ReadTruncateStatementFromFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"\" description=\"A statement to be executed when truncating the database table\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction/GenerateTruncateStatement\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Truncate statement\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"TruncateStatement\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"><Callouts><Callout callout=\"generateSQL\" calloutDescription=\"Generate a truncate table statement\" calloutFilterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction/GenerateTruncateStatement/ReadTruncateStatementFromFile\" calloutFilterValue=\"1\" calloutLabel=\"Generate\" calloutRequiresConnection=\"true\" calloutType=\"builder\"><CalloutArgument name=\"statementType\">TruncateTableSQL</CalloutArgument></Callout></Callouts></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"true\" description=\"Select Yes to perform table action first. Select No to run Before SQL statements first.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction\" filterValue=\"1 2 3\" label=\"Perform table action first\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"TableActionFirst\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property description=\"Transaction properties\" inputLinkCountConstraint=\"single\" label=\"Transaction\" name=\"Transaction\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"2000\" description=\"Number of records per transaction. The value 0 means all available records\" inputLinkCountConstraint=\"single\" label=\"Record count\" maxValue=\"999999999\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"RecordCount\" required=\"false\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"0\" description=\"Specify the amount of time to pass before a commit is issued. If you set a small value you force frequent commits and therefore if your program terminates unexpectedly, your table can still contain partial results. However, you may pay a performance penalty because of the high frequency of commits. If you set a large value, DB2 must log a correspondingly large amount of rollback information which may also slow your job.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"2 3 4\" label=\"Time Commit Interval\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"TimeInterval\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property contexts=\"source request\" default=\"0\" description=\"Specify settings for the end of wave handling. None means EOW markers are never inserted, Before means EOW markers are inserted before committing the transaction, After means EOW markers are inserted after committing the transaction\" engines=\"ee\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"1 2\" label=\"End of wave\" name=\"EndOfWave\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">None</Value><Value code=\"1\">Before</Value><Value code=\"2\">After</Value><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether to insert an EOW marker for the last set of records when the number is less than the specified transaction record count value\" label=\"End of data\" name=\"EndOfData\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Transaction grouping allows operations on multiple links to be executed within a single transaction.\" engines=\"se\" inputLinkCountConstraint=\"multiple\" label=\"Enable transaction grouping\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"EnableTransactionGrouping\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" specialFilter=\"1\" type=\"bool\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" description=\"Transaction grouping settings\" engines=\"se\" inputLinkCountConstraint=\"multiple\" label=\"Transaction grouping\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"TransactionGrouping\" required=\"false\" scope=\"link\" specialFilter=\"1\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"The action to be taken when a link is skipped\" label=\"Action on skip\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"ActionOnSkip\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Continue</Value><Value code=\"1\">Rollback</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"The action to be taken when a failure occurs on a link\" label=\"Action on failure\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"ActionOnFailure\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Continue</Value><Value code=\"1\">Rollback</Value></Property></Property><Property description=\"Session properties\" label=\"Session\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"Session\" required=\"false\" scope=\"all\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"1\" description=\"Specifies the isolation level that is used for all database transactions.\" label=\"Isolation level\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"IsolationLevel\" required=\"true\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Read uncommitted</Value><Value code=\"1\">Cursor stability</Value><Value code=\"2\">Read stability</Value><Value code=\"3\">Repeatable read</Value></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether the connector commits transactions manually, or allows the database to commit transactions automatically at its discretion.\" label=\"Auto commit mode\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"AutocommitMode\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Off</Value><Value code=\"1\">On</Value></Property><Property default=\"2000\" description=\"The array size to be used for all read and write database operations\" label=\"Array size\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"ArraySize\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Properties that affect schema reconciliation\" label=\"Schema reconciliation\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"SchemaReconciliation\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Fail if the sizes of numeric and string fields are not compatible when validating the design schema against the database\" label=\"Fail on size mismatch\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnSizeMismatch\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Fail if the types of fields are not compatible when validating the design schema against the database\" label=\"Fail on type mismatch\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnTypeMismatch\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Fail if the code pages of fields are not compatible when validating the design schema against the database\" hidden=\"true\" label=\"Fail on code page mismatch\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnCodePageMismatch\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"true\" description=\"Drop fields that don't exist in the input schema\" label=\"Drop unmatched fields\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"DropUnmatchedFields\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"true\" description=\"Fail the job if a write operation to the target is unsuccessful\" engines=\"ee\" filterForRejectLinks=\"absent\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"0 1 2 3 4 5 7 8\" label=\"Fail on row error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnRowErrorPX\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"false\" description=\"Fail the job if a write operation to the target is unsuccessful\" engines=\"se\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"0 1 2 3 4 5 7 8\" label=\"Fail on row error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnRowErrorSE\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property contexts=\"source request\" default=\"false\" description=\"Enables/disables the ability to specify LOB columns to be passed using locator (reference) information. LOB columns not specified will be passed inline\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Enable LOB references\" name=\"PassLobLocator\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property callout=\"lobCandidateColumns\" calloutDescription=\"Choose columns containing LOBs to be passed by reference (locator). Columns that are not selected will be passed inline\" calloutLabel=\"Available columns\" calloutType=\"builder\" default=\"\" description=\"Use to choose columns containing LOBs to be passed by locator (reference)\" label=\"Columns\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"Column\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\" xsi:type=\"asc:CalloutProperty\"/></Property><Property contexts=\"request\" default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the type of message logged when the lookup query returns more than one match for a set of keys\" engines=\"se\" label=\"Log multiple matches\" name=\"LogMultipleMatches\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">None</Value><Value code=\"1\">Informational</Value><Value code=\"2\">Warning</Value><Value code=\"3\">Fatal</Value></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether to enable the insert buffering optimization in partitioned database environments.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"Insert buffering\" name=\"InsertBuffering\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Default</Value><Value code=\"1\">Off</Value><Value code=\"2\">On</Value><Value code=\"3\">Ignore duplicates</Value><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether arrays should be inserted atomically.  Insert buffering with non-atomic arrays does not report errors accurately.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/Session/InsertBuffering\" filterValue=\"0 2 3\" label=\"Atomic arrays\" name=\"AtomicArrays\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Auto</Value><Value code=\"1\">No</Value><Value code=\"2\">Yes</Value><Value code=\"3\">Simulated</Value></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"0\" description=\"If set to Automatic, the connector will automatically create the temporary work table using an internally generated name.\" label=\"Temporary work table mode\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"TemporaryWorkTable\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/SQL/DirectInsert\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Value code=\"0\">Automatic</Value><Value code=\"1\">Existing</Value><Property description=\"The name of the existing temporary work table.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/Session/TemporaryWorkTable\" filterValue=\"1\" label=\"Table name\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"TableName\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If set to Yes, the temporary work table is truncated before any data is written to it.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/Session/TemporaryWorkTable\" filterValue=\"1\" label=\"Truncate table\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"TruncateTable\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"If set to Yes, the connector will drop the temporary work table.\" label=\"Drop table\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"DropTable\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property contexts=\"source target\" default=\"false\" description=\"Indicates whether external tables are used.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" filterContexts=\"source target\" label=\"Use external tables\" name=\"UseExternalTables\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/SQL/DirectInsert\">false</FilterProperty><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/GenerateSQL\">true</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/WriteMode\">0</FilterProperty></Filter><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/UseETSource\">true</FilterProperty></Filter><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"1\" description=\"The number of rejected records at which the system stops processing and immediately rolls back the load. The default is 1 (that is, a single rejected record results in a rollback)\" label=\"Maximum reject count\" maxValue=\"2147483647\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"MaxErrors\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property contexts=\"source target\" default=\"/tmp\" description=\"Specifies the location where the named pipe used by the load operation should be created. This property applies to Unix systems only.\" label=\"Directory for named pipe (Unix only)\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DirectoryForNamedPipe\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" description=\"Specifies the directory for the log and bad files. If it is left blank, the connector will use the value of the environment variable TMPDIR. If TMPDIR is not defined, it will default to /tmp on Unix and to system temporary directory on Windows.\" label=\"Directory for log files\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"LogDirectory\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property contexts=\"source target\" default=\"\" description=\"Additional options to be passed to the external table statement\" label=\"Other options\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"0\" name=\"OtherOptions\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"false\" description=\"Instructs load to collect statistics during the load according to the profile defined for this table (STATISTICS).\" label=\"Statistics\" name=\"Statistics\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property callout=\"allColumns\" calloutDescription=\"Click here to obtain the list of columns\" calloutLabel=\"Select columns\" calloutType=\"enumerator\" contexts=\"target\" description=\"Generates statistics on the columns. If no column specified, statistics are collected on all columns by default.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/Session/UseExternalTables/Statistics\" filterValue=\"true\" label=\"Statistics on columns\" maxOccurs=\"999999\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"RunStatsOnColumns\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\" xsi:type=\"asc:CalloutProperty\"/></Property></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" description=\"Properties that affect logging\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"0 1 2 3 4 5 7 8\" label=\"Logging\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"Logging\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether to log column values for the first row that fails to be written\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Log column values on first row error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"LogColumnValues\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether to log key columns or all columns for failing statements\" label=\"Log key values only\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"LogKeysOnly\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the delimiter to use between columns\" label=\"Column delimiter\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"Delimiter\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Space</Value><Value code=\"1\">Newline</Value><Value code=\"2\">Tab</Value><Value code=\"3\">Comma</Value></Property></Property></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Before/After SQL properties\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Before/After SQL\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"BeforeAfter\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"\" description=\"Enter the SQL statement or the fully-qualified name of the file that contains the SQL statement to run once before any data is processed.\" label=\"Before SQL\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"before\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to read the SQL statement from the file that is specified in the Before SQL statement property.\" label=\"Read Before SQL statement from file\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"ReadFromFileBeforeSQL\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Abort the job if there is an error executing a command\" label=\"Fail on error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnError\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property default=\"\" description=\"Enter the SQL statement or the fully-qualified name of the file that contains the SQL statement to run once after all data is processed.\" label=\"After SQL\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"after\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to read the SQL statement from the file that is specified in the After SQL statement property.\" label=\"Read After SQL statement from file\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"ReadFromFileAfterSQL\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Abort the job if there is an error executing a command\" label=\"Fail on error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnError\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property default=\"\" description=\"Enter the SQL statement or the fully-qualified name of the file that contains the SQL statement to run once on each node before any data is processed on that node.\" engines=\"ee\" label=\"Before SQL (node)\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"beforeNode\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to read the SQL statement from the file that is specified in the Before SQL (node) statement property.\" label=\"Read Before SQL (node) statement from file\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"ReadFromFileBeforeSQLNode\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Abort the job if there is an error executing a command\" label=\"Fail on error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnError\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property><Property default=\"\" description=\"Enter the SQL statement or the fully-qualified name of the file that contains the SQL statement to run once one each node after all data is processed on that node.\" engines=\"ee\" label=\"After SQL (node)\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"afterNode\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to read the SQL statement from the file that is specified in the After SQL (node) statement property.\" label=\"Read After SQL (node) statement from file\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" name=\"ReadFromFileAfterSQLNode\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Abort the job if there is an error executing a command\" label=\"Fail on error\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"0\" name=\"FailOnError\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"0\" deprecated=\"false\" description=\"Determines how records should be ordered across multiple links.\" engines=\"ee\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" hidden=\"false\" inputLinkCountConstraint=\"multiple\" label=\"Record ordering\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"RecordOrdering\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">All records</Value><Value code=\"1\">First record</Value><Value code=\"2\">Ordered</Value><Property default=\"false\" description=\"A column to be used for sorting.\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/RecordOrdering\" filterValue=\"2\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"Key column\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"KeyColumn\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"category\"><Property callout=\"columns\" calloutDescription=\"Choose columns to define cross-link ordering\" calloutLabel=\"Available columns\" calloutType=\"builder\" description=\"The name of a column to be used for sorting.\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"Column name\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"ColumnName\" required=\"true\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"string\" xsi:type=\"asc:CalloutProperty\"><CalloutArgument name=\"columnSelection\">commonInput</CalloutArgument></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether sorting should be in ascending or descending order.\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"Sort order\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"SortOrder\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Ascending</Value><Value code=\"1\">Descending</Value></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether null values should appear before or after non-null values.\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"Null order\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"NullOrder\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Before</Value><Value code=\"1\">After</Value></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether strings should be compared using a case sensitive or insensitive comparison.\" filterContexts=\"all\" filterEngines=\"all\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"Case sensitive\" maxOccurs=\"1\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"false\" name=\"CaseSensitive\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"bool\"/></Property></Property><Property default=\"2\" description=\"Specifies the type of reoptimization that is done by DB2.\" label=\"Reoptimization\" name=\"ReOptimization\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"2\">None</Value><Value code=\"3\">Once</Value><Value code=\"4\">Always</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"Specifies the lock wait strategy that is used when a lock cannot be obtained immediately.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"3\" filterContexts=\"target\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"0 1 2 3 4 5 7 8\" label=\"Lock wait mode\" name=\"LockWaitMode\" required=\"false\" scope=\"stage\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Return an SQLCODE and SQLSTATE</Value><Value code=\"1\">Use the lock timeout database configuration parameter</Value><Value code=\"2\">Wait indefinitely</Value><Value code=\"3\">User specified</Value><Property description=\"Time to wait for a lock\" label=\"Lock wait time\" maxValue=\"32767\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"LockWaitModeTime\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property contexts=\"target request\" description=\"Specifies the pad character that is used in the WHERE clause for string columns that are smaller than the column size.\" label=\"Pad character\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"PadCharacter\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"false\" description=\"By default the connector runs one player process per database partition. If you want to force the connector to run fewer player processes, set this property to Yes\" engines=\"ee\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Limit parallelism\" name=\"LimitParallelism\" partitionType=\"connector\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/WriteMode\">6</FilterProperty></Filter><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/WriteMode\">0 1 2 3 4 5 8</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/Session/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty></Filter></Filter><Property contexts=\"target\" description=\"The total number of player processes across all processing nodes.\" label=\"Total number of player processes\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PlayerProcessLimit\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" default=\"false\" description=\"Determines whether the target table is on DB2 for z/OS.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/WriteMode\" filterValue=\"6\" label=\"Bulk load to DB2 on z/OS\" name=\"LoadToZOS\" required=\"false\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Load method to be used for loading input data into DB2 for z/OS.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/Transfer/TransferType\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"Load method\" name=\"LoadMethod\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">MVS dataset(s)</Value><Value code=\"1\">Batch pipe(s)</Value><Value code=\"2\">USS pipe(s)</Value></Property><Property description=\"Transfer properties\" label=\"Transfer\" name=\"Transfer\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Determines the method of transferring data to the z/OS machine.\" label=\"Transfer type\" name=\"TransferType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">ftp</Value><Value code=\"1\">sftp</Value><Value code=\"2\">lftp</Value></Property><Property description=\"Name of the target machine to which the data is sent.\" label=\"Transfer to\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"TransferTo\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Determines the user name for transferring.\" label=\"User\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"User\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Determines the password for transferring.\" label=\"Password\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Password\" required=\"false\" type=\"protectedstring\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the location where the data files will be created before transfer to z/OS.\" label=\"Directory for data files\" maxLength=\"4096\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataFilePath\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"The presence of this option indicates that HFS files is to be used and gives the directory name where the files will be created. The value should be a fully qualified HFS directory name.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/Transfer/TransferType\" filterValue=\"1 2\" label=\"HFS file directory\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"USSFileDirectory\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"User-entered command sent just before data transfer begins.  FTP example:  quote site vcount=7 datakeepalive=60\" label=\"Transfer command\" maxLength=\"2000\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"TransferCmd\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Select Yes to try to establish a connection again when the initial attempt to connect is unsuccessful.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/Transfer/TransferType\" filterValue=\"0 2\" label=\"Retry on connection failure\" name=\"RetryConnection\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"3\" description=\"Enter the number of times to try to establish a connection after a failure on the initial attempt.\" label=\"Number of retries\" maxValue=\"999999999\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"RetryCount\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"10\" description=\"Enter the time in seconds to wait between retries to establish a connection.\" label=\"Interval between retries\" maxValue=\"999999999\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"RetryInterval\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/></Property></Property><Property description=\"This option identifies a prefix to be used when creating MVS dataset names.  If omitted, the transfer user name is used.\" label=\"DSN prefix\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DSNPrefix\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"If the data is to be transferred to a Batch pipes system on z/OS, this option identifies its name.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"1\" label=\"Batch pipe system ID\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"BatchPipeSystemID\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"The presence of this option indicates that USS piping is to be used and gives the directory name where the pipes will be created. The value should be a fully qualified USS directory name.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"2\" label=\"USS pipe directory\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"USSPipeDirectory\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"LOAD will not actually be executed, only MVS datasets are created.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"File(s) only\" name=\"FilesOnly\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"SYSDA\" description=\"This option specifies the device type to be used for various datasets that the LOAD utility may need.  If omitted, the default is SYSDA.\" label=\"Device type\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DeviceType\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"If this option is present, then only the indicated partition will be loaded.  If this option is omitted, all partitions of the DB2 for z/OS database table will be loaded.\" label=\"Partition number\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PartitionNumber\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"1000\" description=\"This option specifies an estimated count of the total number of rows to be loaded into all partitions combined.  This estimate is used to calculate the amount of disk space which will be needed on z/OS for various datasets.  If not present, a row estimate of 1000 is used.\" label=\"Row count estimate\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"RowCountEstimate\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"This option requests that statistics be displayed at the end of the load.\" label=\"Statistics\" name=\"Statistics\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">None</Value><Value code=\"1\">All</Value><Value code=\"2\">Index</Value><Value code=\"3\">Table</Value></Property><Property default=\"DB2ZLOAD\" description=\"This is a unique identifier within DB2 for the execution of the LOAD utility.  The default value is DB2ZLOAD.\" label=\"Utility ID\" maxLength=\"16\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"UtilityID\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Level of application's concurrent access to the table space or partition. Parameter's value corresponds to SHRLEVEL option of LOAD command.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/TableAction\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"Concurrent access level\" name=\"ShrLevel\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">NONE</Value><Value code=\"1\">REFERENCE</Value><Value code=\"2\">CHANGE</Value></Property><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Select Yes to add records to the end of the table if the table space is not empty or No to load data into an empty table space. The value corresponds to the RESUME option value in the LOAD command.\" label=\"Keep existing records in table space\" name=\"Resume\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/TableAction\">0</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/ShrLevel\">0</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Indicates whether logging is to occur during the load process.\" label=\"Load with logging\" name=\"LoadWithLogging\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether or not the table space is set to the copy-pending status.  (Applicable only when Load with logging = No)\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadWithLogging\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Set copy-pending\" name=\"SetCopyPending\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the input dataset encoding\" label=\"Encoding\" name=\"Encoding\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">EBCDIC</Value><Value code=\"1\">ASCII</Value><Value code=\"2\">UNICODE</Value><Value code=\"3\">CCSID</Value><Property description=\"The IANA character set name for the encoding.  If not specified, ibm-1047-s390 will be used for EBCDIC, ASCII for ASCII, and UTF-16BE for UNICODE.\" label=\"Character set\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"CharacterSet\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"The IANA character set name for the graphic encoding.  If not specified, UTF-16BE is the default.\" label=\"Graphic character set\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"GraphicCharacterSet\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the coded character set identifier (CCSID) for SBCS data, Mixed data, and DBCS data in the input file.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/Encoding\" filterValue=\"3\" label=\"CCSID\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"CCSID\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether to run an Image-copy function after Load\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"1 2 3\" label=\"Image-copy function\" name=\"ImageCopyFunction\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">No</Value><Value code=\"1\">Full</Value><Value code=\"2\">Concurrent</Value><Value code=\"3\">Incremental</Value><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Scope of the image-copy\" label=\"Scope\" name=\"Scope\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Full</Value><Value code=\"1\">Single partition</Value></Property><Property description=\"Image-copy file attributes\" label=\"Image-copy file\" name=\"ImageCopyFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property description=\"Dataset name used by the Load utility. If empty (default), then a dataset name is generated using the DSN prefix property.\" label=\"Dataset name\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DatasetName\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the number of buffers to use (BUFNO). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Number of buffers\" maxValue=\"99\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"NumberOfBuffers\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the device number, device type (generic), or group name for the data set (UNIT). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Unit\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Unit\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS data class (DATACLAS). The name must be a valid SMS data class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Data class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS management class (MGMTCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS management class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Management class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"ManagementClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS storage class (STORCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS storage class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Storage class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"StorageClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies a list of volume serial numbers for this allocation (VOLUMES(?)). The value or list of values may be entered by the user with or without enclosing parentheses. In the TEMPLATE statement, however, the parentheses are required. So, if the user does not enter them, the syntax generator should add them. The value for this property is a comma-separated list of string values. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Volume(s)\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Volumes\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"File disposition properties\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"File disposition\" name=\"FileDisposition\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"This option specifies the disposition status of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility (DISP(?,?,?)). Specify the disposition status of the input data set used by load utility. This property is disabled when batch pipe system ID has any value. The default value is Replace. The valid values for this property are: Replace - Deletes an existing data set and creates a new data set (NEW). New - Indicates that the file does not currently exist (NEW). Old - Overwrites an existing data set or fails if the data set does not exist (OLD). Share - Identical to Old except that several jobs can read from the data set at the same time (SHR). Append - Appends to the end of an existing data set or creates a new data set if it does not already exist (MOD).\" label=\"Status\" name=\"Status\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"1\">New</Value><Value code=\"2\">Old</Value><Value code=\"3\">Share</Value><Value code=\"4\">Append</Value></Property><Property default=\"2\" description=\"This option specifies the normal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Normal termination\" name=\"NormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property><Property default=\"2\" description=\"This option specifies the abnormal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Abnormal termination\" name=\"AbnormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space allocation unit type (SPACE(?,?)). Valid values are Cylinders (CYL) and Tracks (TRK). The default value is Cylinders.\" label=\"Space type\" name=\"SpaceType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Cylinders</Value><Value code=\"1\">Tracks</Value></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space primary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Primary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PrimaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space secondary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Secondary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"SecondaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether or not to create a backup of the image-copy file\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Image-copy backup file\" name=\"ImageCopyBackupFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property description=\"Dataset name used by the Load utility. If empty (default), then a dataset name is generated using the DSN prefix property.\" label=\"Dataset name\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DatasetName\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the number of buffers to use (BUFNO). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Number of buffers\" maxValue=\"99\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"NumberOfBuffers\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the device number, device type (generic), or group name for the data set (UNIT). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Unit\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Unit\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS data class (DATACLAS). The name must be a valid SMS data class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Data class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS management class (MGMTCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS management class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Management class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"ManagementClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS storage class (STORCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS storage class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Storage class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"StorageClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies a list of volume serial numbers for this allocation (VOLUMES(?)). The value or list of values may be entered by the user with or without enclosing parentheses. In the TEMPLATE statement, however, the parentheses are required. So, if the user does not enter them, the syntax generator should add them. The value for this property is a comma-separated list of string values. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Volume(s)\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Volumes\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"File disposition properties\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"File disposition\" name=\"FileDisposition\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"This option specifies the disposition status of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility (DISP(?,?,?)). Specify the disposition status of the input data set used by load utility. This property is disabled when batch pipe system ID has any value. The default value is Replace. The valid values for this property are: Replace - Deletes an existing data set and creates a new data set (NEW). New - Indicates that the file does not currently exist (NEW). Old - Overwrites an existing data set or fails if the data set does not exist (OLD). Share - Identical to Old except that several jobs can read from the data set at the same time (SHR). Append - Appends to the end of an existing data set or creates a new data set if it does not already exist (MOD).\" label=\"Status\" name=\"Status\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"1\">New</Value><Value code=\"2\">Old</Value><Value code=\"3\">Share</Value><Value code=\"4\">Append</Value></Property><Property default=\"2\" description=\"This option specifies the normal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Normal termination\" name=\"NormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property><Property default=\"2\" description=\"This option specifies the abnormal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Abnormal termination\" name=\"AbnormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space allocation unit type (SPACE(?,?)). Valid values are Cylinders (CYL) and Tracks (TRK). The default value is Cylinders.\" label=\"Space type\" name=\"SpaceType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Cylinders</Value><Value code=\"1\">Tracks</Value></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space primary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Primary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PrimaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space secondary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Secondary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"SecondaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Specifies whether or not to create the image-copy recovery file\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Recovery file\" name=\"RecoveryFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property description=\"Dataset name used by the Load utility. If empty (default), then a dataset name is generated using the DSN prefix property.\" label=\"Dataset name\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DatasetName\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the number of buffers to use (BUFNO). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Number of buffers\" maxValue=\"99\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"NumberOfBuffers\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the device number, device type (generic), or group name for the data set (UNIT). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Unit\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Unit\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS data class (DATACLAS). The name must be a valid SMS data class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Data class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS management class (MGMTCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS management class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Management class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"ManagementClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS storage class (STORCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS storage class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Storage class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"StorageClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies a list of volume serial numbers for this allocation (VOLUMES(?)). The value or list of values may be entered by the user with or without enclosing parentheses. In the TEMPLATE statement, however, the parentheses are required. So, if the user does not enter them, the syntax generator should add them. The value for this property is a comma-separated list of string values. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Volume(s)\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Volumes\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"File disposition properties\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"File disposition\" name=\"FileDisposition\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"This option specifies the disposition status of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility (DISP(?,?,?)). Specify the disposition status of the input data set used by load utility. This property is disabled when batch pipe system ID has any value. The default value is Replace. The valid values for this property are: Replace - Deletes an existing data set and creates a new data set (NEW). New - Indicates that the file does not currently exist (NEW). Old - Overwrites an existing data set or fails if the data set does not exist (OLD). Share - Identical to Old except that several jobs can read from the data set at the same time (SHR). Append - Appends to the end of an existing data set or creates a new data set if it does not already exist (MOD).\" label=\"Status\" name=\"Status\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"1\">New</Value><Value code=\"2\">Ol