is disabled when batch pipe system ID has any value. The default value is Replace. The valid values for this property are: Replace - Deletes an existing data set and creates a new data set (NEW). New - Indicates that the file does not currently exist (NEW). Old - Overwrites an existing data set or fails if the data set does not exist (OLD). Share - Identical to Old except that several jobs can read from the data set at the same time (SHR). Append - Appends to the end of an existing data set or creates a new data set if it does not already exist (MOD).\" label=\"Status\" name=\"Status\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"1\">New</Value><Value code=\"2\">Old</Value><Value code=\"3\">Share</Value><Value code=\"4\">Append</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"This option specifies the normal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Normal termination\" name=\"NormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"This option specifies the abnormal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Abnormal termination\" name=\"AbnormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space allocation unit type (SPACE(?,?)). Valid values are Cylinders (CYL) and Tracks (TRK). The default value is Cylinders.\" label=\"Space type\" name=\"SpaceType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Cylinders</Value><Value code=\"1\">Tracks</Value></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space primary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Primary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PrimaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space secondary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Secondary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"SecondaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property description=\"Work2 dataset attributes\" label=\"Work2 dataset\" name=\"Work2DataSet\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property description=\"Dataset name used by the Load utility. If empty (default), then a dataset name is generated using the DSN prefix property.\" label=\"Dataset name\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DatasetName\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the number of buffers to use (BUFNO). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Number of buffers\" maxValue=\"99\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"NumberOfBuffers\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the device number, device type (generic), or group name for the data set (UNIT). If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Unit\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Unit\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS data class (DATACLAS). The name must be a valid SMS data class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Data class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS management class (MGMTCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS management class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Management class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"ManagementClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the SMS storage class (STORCLAS). The name must be a valid SMS storage class and must not exceed 8 characters in length. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Storage class\" maxLength=\"8\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"StorageClass\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies a list of volume serial numbers for this allocation (VOLUMES(?)). The value or list of values may be entered by the user with or without enclosing parentheses. In the TEMPLATE statement, however, the parentheses are required. So, if the user does not enter them, the syntax generator should add them. The value for this property is a comma-separated list of string values. If empty (default), then the property is not used.\" label=\"Volume(s)\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"Volumes\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"File disposition properties\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS/LoadMethod\" filterValue=\"0\" label=\"File disposition\" name=\"FileDisposition\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"This option specifies the disposition status of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility (DISP(?,?,?)). Specify the disposition status of the input data set used by load utility. This property is disabled when batch pipe system ID has any value. The default value is Replace. The valid values for this property are: Replace - Deletes an existing data set and creates a new data set (NEW). New - Indicates that the file does not currently exist (NEW). Old - Overwrites an existing data set or fails if the data set does not exist (OLD). Share - Identical to Old except that several jobs can read from the data set at the same time (SHR). Append - Appends to the end of an existing data set or creates a new data set if it does not already exist (MOD).\" label=\"Status\" name=\"Status\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"1\">New</Value><Value code=\"2\">Old</Value><Value code=\"3\">Share</Value><Value code=\"4\">Append</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"This option specifies the normal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Normal termination\" name=\"NormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"This option specifies the abnormal termination disposition of the dataset(s) used by the LOAD utility: Keep (KEEP), Delete (DELETE), Catalog (CATLG), Uncatalog (UNCATLG).\" label=\"Abnormal termination\" name=\"AbnormalTermination\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Keep</Value><Value code=\"1\">Delete</Value><Value code=\"2\">Catalog</Value><Value code=\"3\">Uncatalog</Value></Property></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space allocation unit type (SPACE(?,?)). Valid values are Cylinders (CYL) and Tracks (TRK). The default value is Cylinders.\" label=\"Space type\" name=\"SpaceType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Cylinders</Value><Value code=\"1\">Tracks</Value></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space primary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Primary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"PrimaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the z/OS disk space secondary allocation amount. The range of values is from 1 to 1677215. If empty (default), then its value equals computed (from the row estimate) space requirements in cylinders or tracks, respectively to Space type setting. For Map dataset, the resulting value is doubled.\" label=\"Secondary allocation\" maxValue=\"1677215\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"SecondaryAllocation\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"target\" description=\"Specifies the properties that control the bulk load operations.\" label=\"Load control\" name=\"LoadControl\" required=\"false\" transactionModels=\"local\" type=\"category\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/WriteMode\">6</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadToZOS\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Property default=\"false\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"Indicates whether external tables are used.\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Use External Tables\" name=\"UseExternalTables\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"false\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"Indicates whether the External Table file data is compressed before the data is transferred, and is decompressed after it is received. This improves overall performance when a large amount of compressible data is being transferred.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Compress file data\" name=\"CompressExternalTables\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Determines the compression algorithm of external table file data.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/CompressExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" label=\"Compression algorithm\" name=\"CompressionType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">GZIP</Value><Value code=\"1\">LZ4</Value></Property></Property><Property default=\"1\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"The number of rejected records at which the system stops processing and immediately rolls back the load. The default is 1 (that is, a single rejected record results in a rollback)\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Maximum reject count\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"MaxErrors\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"For a load operation, the number of rows to skip before beginning to load the data. The default is 0. Because skipped rows are processed before they are skipped, a skipped row is still capable of causing a processing error.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Skip rows\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"SkipRows\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"Additional options to be passed to the external table statement\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Other options\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"0\" name=\"OtherOptions\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property deprecated=\"true\" description=\"Specifies the directory for the log and bad files. If it is left blank, the connector will use the value of the environment variable TMPDIR. If TMPDIR is not defined, it will default to /tmp on Unix and to system temporary directory on Windows.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"true\" hidden=\"false\" label=\"[deprecated] Directory for log files\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"LogDirectory\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the mode where the load operates.\" label=\"Load mode\" name=\"LoadMode\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/TableAction\">0</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Value code=\"0\">Insert</Value><Value code=\"1\">Replace</Value><Value code=\"2\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\" filterValue=\"0\">Restart</Value><Value code=\"3\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\" filterValue=\"0\">Terminate</Value></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies which DB2 load phase is to be restarted. The original input data needs to be reproduced for restarting the Load phase. Build and Delete phases ignore the input data.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMode\" filterValue=\"2\" label=\"Restart phase\" name=\"RestartPhase\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Load</Value><Value code=\"1\">Build</Value><Value code=\"2\">Delete</Value></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Indicates whether there are any LOB or XML columns in the target DB2 table.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Bulk load with LOB or XML column(s)\" name=\"BulkloadWithLobXML\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"1\" description=\"Determines the load method to use.\" label=\"Load method\" name=\"LoadMethod\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty></Filter><Value code=\"0\">Sequential File(s)</Value><Value code=\"1\">Named Pipe(s)</Value></Property><Property description=\"Name of tables where rows that violate constraints will be stored.\" label=\"Exception table name\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"ExceptionTable\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/TableAction\">0 3</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"300\" description=\"Specifies the time in seconds to attempt opening a socket for the load operation before timing out.\" label=\"Load timeout\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"LoadTimeout\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Indicates whether input files should be created without executing the load operation.\" label=\"File(s) only\" name=\"FilesOnly\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">0</FilterProperty></Filter><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">0</FilterProperty></Filter></Filter></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the location where the command file and data file (used by the load operation) should be created.\" label=\"Directory for data and command files\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DataFilePath\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">0</FilterProperty></Filter><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">0</FilterProperty></Filter></Filter></Property><Property default=\"true\" description=\"Select Yes to remove the intermediate data file after completing the load operation.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/FilesOnly\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Remove intermediate data file\" name=\"RemoveIntermediateDataFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the format of the data in the data file.\" label=\"File type\" name=\"FileType\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Value code=\"0\">ASC</Value><Value code=\"1\">DEL</Value></Property><Property description=\"A list of fully qualified paths or devices to identify the location of the individual LOB files to be loaded.\" label=\"Lob Path List\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"LobPathList\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to add the WITHOUT PROMPTING parameter to the LOAD command in the generated command file.\" label=\"Without prompting\" name=\"WithoutPrompting\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">0</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"/tmp\" description=\"Specifies the location where the named pipe used by the load operation should be created. This property applies to Unix systems only.\" label=\"Directory for named pipe (Unix only)\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DirectoryForNamedPipe\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">1</FilterProperty></Filter><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMethod\">1</FilterProperty></Filter></Filter></Property><Property description=\"Specifies the modifiers used with the 'MODIFIED BY' keyword of the DB2 load utility\" label=\"File type modifiers\" name=\"FileTypeModifiers\" required=\"false\" type=\"category\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/BulkloadWithLobXML\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Property description=\"Specifies a fully qualified file path to use with the 'dumpfile' file type modifier. If no path is specified, the 'dumpfile' modifier is not used\" label=\"Dump file\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DumpFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Clean-up on failures during stage execution.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Clean-up on failure\" name=\"CleanupOnFail\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of records to load before establishing a consistency point.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Save count\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"SaveCount\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of warnings that are allowed before the load operation stops.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Warning count\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"WarningCount\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"The number of physical records to be loaded. Allows a user to load only the first rowcnt rows in a file.\" label=\"Row Count\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"IRowCount\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"loadMsgs.out\" description=\"Specifies the file where DB2 writes diagnostic messages.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Message file\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"MessageFile\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the path name that is used by the DB2 server to store temporary files.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Temporary files directory\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DirectoryForTmpFiles\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"Instructs load to collect statistics during the load according to the profile defined for this table (STATISTICS).\" label=\"Statistics\" name=\"Statistics\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Filter logic=\"or\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/LoadMode\">1</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property callout=\"allColumns\" calloutDescription=\"Click here to obtain the list of columns\" calloutLabel=\"Select columns\" calloutType=\"enumerator\" contexts=\"target\" deprecated=\"true\" description=\"Generates statistics on the columns. If no column specified, statistics are collected on all columns by default.\" label=\"[deprecated] Statistics on columns\" maxOccurs=\"999999\" minOccurs=\"1\" multiline=\"true\" name=\"RunStatsOnColumns\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\" xsi:type=\"asc:CalloutProperty\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/Statistics\">true</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">true</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"The load transaction is marked as non-recoverable.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Non-recoverable load\" name=\"NonRecoverableTX\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the method that is used for making a copy of the loaded data.\" label=\"Copy loaded data\" name=\"CopyLoadedData\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/NonRecoverableTX\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter><Value code=\"0\">No copy</Value><Value code=\"1\">Use device or directory</Value><Value code=\"2\">Use shared library</Value><Value code=\"3\">Use Tivoli to make a copy</Value><Property default=\"\" description=\"A comma-separated list of devices or directories where the copy is generated.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/CopyLoadedData\" filterValue=\"1\" label=\"Loaded data copy location\" maxLength=\"512\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"CopyToDeviceOrDirectory\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"\" description=\"Specifies the name of the library that is used to generate the copy.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/CopyLoadedData\" filterValue=\"2\" label=\"Library used to copy\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"CopyLoadLibraryName\" required=\"true\" type=\"string\"/></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If selected, the table remains in quiesced exclusive state after the load operation.\" hidden=\"true\" label=\"Hold quiesce\" name=\"HoldQuiesce\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of pages (size 4KB) that are used as buffered space for transferring data within the load utility.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Data buffer size\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"DataBufferSize\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of pages (size 4KB) of memory that are used for sorting index keys during a load operation.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/IndexingMode\" filterValue=\"0 1 2\" label=\"Sort buffer size\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"SortBufferSize\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Filter logic=\"and\"><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/IndexingMode\">false</FilterProperty><FilterProperty logic=\"or\" property=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\">false</FilterProperty></Filter></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of processes or threads that the load utility spawns for processing records.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"CPU parallelism\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"CPUParallelism\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of processes or threads that the load utility spawns for writing data.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Disk parallelism\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"DiskParallelism\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies whether indexes are rebuilt or extended incrementally.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Indexing mode\" name=\"IndexingMode\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Automatic selection</Value><Value code=\"1\">Rebuild table indexes</Value><Value code=\"2\">Extend existing indexes</Value><Value code=\"3\">Do not update table indexes</Value></Property><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the level of access on the table that is to be loaded.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"1\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Allow access mode\" name=\"AllowAccessMode\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">No access</Value><Value code=\"1\">Read</Value><Property description=\"Specifies the table space that is used for building a shadow copy of the index if the indexes are being rebuilt.\" label=\"Name of table space\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"TableSpace\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/></Property><Property default=\"1\" description=\"Specifies whether the check pending state of the loaded table is immediately cascaded to all descendants.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Check pending cascade\" name=\"CheckPendingCascade\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Immediate</Value><Value code=\"1\">Deferred</Value></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If selected, the load operation forces off other applications that hold conflicting locks.\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/UseExternalTables\" filterValue=\"false\" label=\"Lock with force\" name=\"LockWithForce\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If selected, data is loaded into a partitioned table.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Partitioned database configuration\" name=\"PartitionedDBConfig\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property description=\"List of database partition numbers (OUTPUT_DBPARTNUMS). The database partition numbers represent the database partitions on which the load operation is to be performed. Items in the list must be separated by commas.\" label=\"Output partition numbers\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"OutputDBPartNums\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property description=\"List of database partition numbers that are used in the distribution process (PARTITIONING_DBPARTNUMS). Items in the list must be separated by commas.\" label=\"Partitioning partition numbers\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"PartitioningDBPartNums\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"25\" description=\"Specifies the maximum number of partitioning agents to be used in a load session (MAX_NUM_PART_AGENTS).\" label=\"Maximum partitioning agents\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"MaxNumPartAgents\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property default=\"1\" description=\"Specifies the reaction of the load operation to errors that occur on individual partitions (ISOLATE_PART_ERRS).\" label=\"Isolate partition errors\" name=\"IsolatePartErrors\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"><Value code=\"0\">Setup errors only</Value><Value code=\"1\">Load errors only</Value><Value code=\"2\">Setup and load errors</Value><Value code=\"3\">No isolation</Value></Property><Property default=\"100\" description=\"Specifies the number of megabytes of data to load before generating a progress message (STATUS_INTERVAL).\" label=\"Status interval\" maxValue=\"4000\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"StatusInterval\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Specifies the range of TCP ports that are used to create sockets for internal communications (PORT_RANGE).\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Port range\" name=\"PortRange\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property description=\"Lower port number of the port range\" label=\"Lower port number\" maxValue=\"65535\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"MinValue\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"Higher port number of the port range\" label=\"Higher port number\" maxValue=\"65535\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"MaxValue\" required=\"true\" type=\"int\"/></Property><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If selected, data records are checked for truncation at input and output (CHECK_TRUNCATION).\" label=\"Check truncation\" name=\"CheckTruncation\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"0\" description=\"Specifies the number of records to trace in a dump of the data conversion process and the output of the hashing values (TRACE).\" label=\"Trace\" minValue=\"0\" name=\"Trace\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/><Property description=\"If this option is specified, the load utility generates a database partition distribution file with the given name (DISTFILE).\" label=\"Partitioned distribution file\" maxLength=\"256\" minLength=\"1\" name=\"DistFile\" required=\"false\" type=\"string\"/><Property default=\"false\" description=\"If selected, the partition map header is not included in the partition file.\" hidden=\"true\" label=\"Omit header\" name=\"OmitHeader\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"/><Property default=\"-1\" description=\"Specifies the database partition where statistics are collected (RUN_STAT_DBPARTNUM).\" filterProperty=\"/Usage/LoadControl/Statistics\" filterValue=\"true\" label=\"Partition collecting statistics\" maxValue=\"32767\" minValue=\"-1\" name=\"RunStatDBPartnum\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property></Property><Property contexts=\"source\" default=\"false\" description=\"Select Yes to limit the number of rows that are returned by the connector.\" filterChildPropertiesOnValue=\"true\" label=\"Limit number of returned rows\" name=\"LimitRows\" required=\"false\" type=\"bool\"><Property default=\"1000\" description=\"Enter the maximum number of rows that will be returned by the connector.\" label=\"Limit\" minValue=\"1\" name=\"Limit\" required=\"false\" type=\"int\"/></Property></Usage></Properties><MetaBag><MetaProperty Name=\"InputLinkOrder\" Owner=\"APT\" Value=\"#\"/><MetaProperty Name=\"OutputLinkOrder\" Owner=\"APT\" Value=\"!#\"/></MetaBag><ModelMappings><DataConnection><ConnectionString>/Connection/Database</ConnectionString><Username>/Connection/Username</Username><Password>/Connection/Password</Password><Private name=\"Instance\">/Connection/Instance</Private><Private name=\"ConnectionType\">/Connection/ConnectionType</Private><Private name=\"Hostname\">/Connection/Hostname</Private><Private name=\"Port\">/Connection/Port</Private><Private name=\"SslConnection\">/Connection/SslConnection</Private><Private name=\"SslCertificate\">/Connection/SslCertificate</Private><Private name=\"Options\">/Connection/Options</Private><Private name=\"AuthenticationType\">/Connection/AuthenticationType</Private><Private name=\"ApiKey\">/Connection/ApiKey</Private><Private name=\"DB2ClientLibFile\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/DB2ClientLibFile</Private><Private name=\"Conductor\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor</Private><Private name=\"ConductorInstance\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor/Instance</Private><Private name=\"ConductorDatabase\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor/Database</Private><Private name=\"ConductorUsername\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor/Username</Private><Private name=\"ConductorPassword\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor/Password</Private><Private name=\"ConductorDB2ClientLibFile\" usage=\"runtime\">/Connection/Conductor/DB2ClientLibFile</Private></DataConnection></ModelMappings></asc:Connector>"
